title: What channel is Kansas City Royals-Toronto Blue Jays on? TV, live stream for ALCS Game 2
text:
What channel is Kansas City Royals-Toronto Blue Jays on? TV, live stream for ALCS Game 2 Salvador Perez Kansas City's Salvador Perez hits a solo home run against Toronto Blue Jays' starter Marco Estrada during the fourth inning of Game 1 of the American League Championship Series in Kansas City on Friday. (Nathan Denette | The Associated Press) 
The Kansas City Royals host the Toronto Blue Jays in Game 2 of the American League Championship Series on Saturday afternoon. 
The Royals lead the best-of-7 series 1-0 after a win in Game 1 on Friday. 
Toronto's David Price will get the start for his team against Kansas City's Yordano Ventura. 
The game starts at 3:30 p.m. and will be televised by Fox Sports 1. 
Here's how to find Fox Sports 1 in Central New York: Time Warner: Channel 400 (SD & HD) Verizon Fios: Channel 583 (HD) and 83 (SD) DirectTV: Channel 219 (SD & HD) Dish Network: Channel 150 (SD &HD) New Visions: Channel 768 (HD) and 83 (SD) 
You can also watch online or through tablets and mobile devices using FOX Sports GO .
